-OH!

05:03.215 --> 05:04.782
-WHAT WERE YOU
DOING ON THAT WALL?

05:05.870 --> 05:07.263
-I WAS JUST RELAXING.

05:08.133 --> 05:09.221
I WAS TRYING TO RELAX.

05:10.571 --> 05:12.312
I GOT A BIG AUDITION
THIS AFTERNOON.

05:12.921 --> 05:15.967
-OH, AN ACTRESS? [LAUGHS]

05:16.098 --> 05:17.708
-A WAITRESS, ACTUALLY.

05:19.057 --> 05:21.582
BUT HOPEFULLY NOT
AFTER TODAY'S AUDITION.

05:22.844 --> 05:24.193
-WELL, COME ON.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.368
LET'S GET YOU OUT OF
THESE WET CLOTHES.

05:26.891 --> 05:28.719
-OH MY GOD!
-MATT: WHAT'S WRONG?

05:29.459 --> 05:31.679
-MY MONEY, OH!

05:32.941 --> 05:34.508
IT MUST HAVE FALLEN
OUT IN THE WATER.

05:35.204 --> 05:36.901
-I'M SORRY. COME ON.

05:44.126 --> 05:44.996
-[SIGH]

05:53.788 --> 05:54.658
-MITCH.

05:55.311 --> 05:56.617
-HEY!

05:56.747 --> 05:58.270
-I'D LIKE YOU TO
MEET SCOTT DANIELS.

06:02.623 --> 06:04.276
SCOTT, THIS IS MITCH BUCHANNON.

06:04.929 --> 06:05.887
-GOOD TO MEET YOU, MITCH.

06:06.017 --> 06:06.888
-HOW YOU DOING?

06:07.497 --> 06:09.194
-SCOTT'S A COASTGUARD
RESCUE SWIMMER.

06:09.325 --> 06:10.892
WE MET WHILE I WAS ON
THE EXCHANGE PROGRAM

06:11.022 --> 06:12.154
WHILE YOU WERE OUT OF TOWN.

06:12.284 --> 06:14.069
-GREAT.

06:14.199 --> 06:15.723
-I GOT TRANSFERRED DOWN HERE
FROM SAN FRANCISCO LAST MONTH.

06:16.898 --> 06:17.986
-WELL, YOU LIKE IT DOWN HERE?

06:19.596 --> 06:20.902
-YEAH, I LOVE LA.

06:26.298 --> 06:27.822
-SCOTT TRAINED
WITH THE NAVY SEALS.

06:28.475 --> 06:29.432
-REALLY?

06:29.998 --> 06:31.695
-WELL, IT WAS JUST
FOR A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

06:31.826 --> 06:33.349
WE GET CALLED ON
BY OTHER SERVICES

06:33.480 --> 06:35.395
TO PERFORM SEARCH AND
RESCUE OPERATIONS.

06:36.570 --> 06:39.268
-WELL, I THINK YOU GUYS
HAVE DONE ENOUGH BONDING.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.488
WE MUSTN'T DISTRACT
THE LIFEGUARD.

06:42.489 --> 06:43.359
SEE YOU, MITCH.

06:44.012 --> 06:44.926
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

06:49.626 --> 06:51.280
-[DRYER DINGS]

07:00.289 --> 07:02.291
-MATT: [KNOCKS] HELLO?
-HEY!

07:03.684 --> 07:05.468
-HERE WE GO.

07:05.599 --> 07:07.862
-I FILLED OUT EVERYTHING LIKE
YOU SAID, NAME AND ADDRESS.

07:07.992 --> 07:09.298
I DON'T HAVE A PHONE YET.

07:10.604 --> 07:12.344
OH, THESE ARE NICE AND WARM!

07:13.694 --> 07:14.956
THANK YOU, UM--

07:15.478 --> 07:17.828
-MATT, MATT BRODY.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

07:19.700 --> 07:22.093
OKAY, RACHEL HENDERSON.

07:23.051 --> 07:26.620
STAY OFF THE SEA WALLS, AND
GOOD LUCK ON YOUR AUDITION.

07:27.925 --> 07:30.275
-THANKS, BUT I CAN'T GO NOW.

07:31.146 --> 07:32.364
-WHY NOT?

07:32.495 --> 07:34.410
-WELL, I DON'T
HAVE MY HEAD SHOTS.

07:34.541 --> 07:35.977
YOU KNOW, AFTER
YOU READ FOR A PART

07:36.107 --> 07:38.109
YOU GOTTA LEAVE YOUR
HEAD SHOT AND RESUME.

07:39.415 --> 07:42.331
WELL, I DON'T-- I HAD THESE
GREAT PICTURES TAKEN,

07:42.462 --> 07:44.812
BUT NOW I DON'T HAVE THE
MONEY TO PAY FOR THEM.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.469
OH, WELL, I PROBABLY WOULDN'T
HAVE GOTTEN IT ANYWAY.

07:52.210 --> 07:53.690
-HOW MUCH DO YOU NEED?

07:57.912 --> 07:59.522
-OH, NO. I COULDN'T ASK.

08:00.958 --> 08:03.004
-YOU'RE NOT ASKING;
I'M OFFERING.

08:10.707 --> 08:15.843
-HEY. THANKS, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE DOING THIS FOR ME.

08:15.973 --> 08:18.019
-HEY, WHO KNOWS,
YOU COULD PROBABLY BE

08:18.149 --> 08:19.455
THE NEXT JULIA ROBERTS.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.196
-WELL, LOOK, I'M
WAITRESSING TONIGHT, SO

08:21.326 --> 08:22.632
I'LL PAY YOU BACK FIRST
THING IN THE MORNING.

08:22.763 --> 08:24.025
WHAT TIME DO YOU GET HERE?

08:24.155 --> 08:25.635
-MATT: 9:00.
-9:00.

08:25.766 --> 08:26.854
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

08:28.595 --> 08:29.770
THANK YOU, MATT.

09:25.086 --> 09:29.003
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

10:04.865 --> 10:06.562
-SORRY, I COULDN'T SEE HIM.

10:06.693 --> 10:09.565
-IT'S OKAY. IT'S
NOT YOUR FAULT.

10:10.958 --> 10:11.959
YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:12.089 --> 10:13.743
-YEAH, YEAH, I'M FINE, THANKS.

10:13.874 --> 10:15.092
THAT WAS VERY CLOSE THOUGH, HUH.

10:15.223 --> 10:16.964
-YEAH.

10:17.094 --> 10:19.793
WELL THE BEACH IS NOT THE SAFEST
PLACE TO SLEEP, YOU KNOW.

10:19.923 --> 10:24.580
-I APOLOGIZE.
IT'S JUST THAT I WAS VERY
TIRED AND-- FORGIVE ME.

10:24.711 --> 10:26.408
I'M SORRY TO HAVE BOTHERED--
-HANG ON A SECOND.

10:26.974 --> 10:28.758
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU COULD
USE A CUP OF COFFEE.

10:28.889 --> 10:31.326
-OH, NO, I COULDN'T IMPOSE.
-COME ON, I'M BUYING. COME ON.

10:42.424 --> 10:43.817
ANOTHER CUP OF COFFEE, MR KREBS?

10:43.947 --> 10:45.470
-OH YEAH, THAT WOULD BE GREAT.
THANKS.

10:45.601 --> 10:46.863
AND PLEASE CALL ME HENRY.

10:48.299 --> 10:50.345
-SO YOU SAY YOUR DAUGHTER
RAN AWAY TWO MONTHS AGO?

10:50.475 --> 10:51.520
-YES.

10:52.042 --> 10:54.741
WE LIVE IN OHIO, MY
WIFE AND I AND NANCY.

10:55.480 --> 10:56.917
NANCY IS OUR DAUGHTER.

10:57.874 --> 10:59.920
MAYBE I WAS TOO
STRICT. I DON'T KNOW,

11:00.660 --> 11:03.314
BUT ANYWAY, ONE MORNING SHE
JUST LEFT FOR LOS ANGELES

11:03.445 --> 11:04.446
AND DIDN'T SAY WHERE.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.709
I KNOW THAT NANCY
LOVES THE BEACH,

11:06.840 --> 11:08.798
SO I FIGURED THAT THIS WOULD BE
THE BEST PLACE TO START LOOKING.

11:09.494 --> 11:10.626
DO YOU HAVE ANY CHILDREN?

11:11.279 --> 11:13.455
-YEAH, YEAH, I
HAVE A SON, HOBIE.

11:13.585 --> 11:15.500
-OH, YEAH, WELL,
I HAVE THREE SONS.

11:15.631 --> 11:17.111
AND FIVE DAUGHTERS.

11:18.503 --> 11:19.809
NANCY IS THE YOUNGEST.

11:24.074 --> 11:25.859
I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO TAKE HER HOME.

11:25.989 --> 11:28.688
SHE'S A BIG GIRL. SHE CAN
MAKE HER OWN DECISIONS.

11:29.645 --> 11:31.299
I JUST CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.

11:31.952 --> 11:32.735
-GOODBYE?

11:34.215 --> 11:36.957
-THE DOCTORS SAY I HAVE
ONLY A FEW MONTHS TO GO.

11:37.740 --> 11:39.524
NOW, THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT I'M GIVING UP HOPE

11:39.655 --> 11:42.745
BY ANY MEANS, IT'S JUST
THAT I WANT TO GET THINGS

11:42.876 --> 11:46.575
STRAIGHTENED OUT BEFORE
THE FINAL GUN GOES OFF.

11:52.886 --> 11:53.669
-HEY, SUMMER.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.410
DO ME A FAVOR, WILL YOU?

11:55.540 --> 11:56.716
HAVE THIS COPIED AND DISTRIBUTED
TO ALL THE LIFEGUARDS.

11:56.846 --> 11:58.195
-SURE, WHO IS SHE?

11:58.326 --> 11:59.719
-RUNAWAY.

11:59.849 --> 12:00.981
HER FATHER DOESN'T
HAVE MUCH TIME LEFT

12:01.111 --> 12:02.634
AND HE WANTS TO TRY TO FIND HER.

12:02.765 --> 12:04.462
-WAIT, WAIT-- MITCH,
I'VE SEEN THIS GIRL.

12:05.028 --> 12:06.769
MATT, HERE LOOK,
TAKE A LOOK AT THAT.

12:06.900 --> 12:08.249
-THAT'S RACHEL.

12:08.379 --> 12:10.686
-NO, ACTUALLY, HER NAME
IS NANCY, NANCY KREBS.

12:10.817 --> 12:12.557
-UH-UH, I PULLED HER OUT OF
THE WATER YESTERDAY.

12:12.688 --> 12:13.733
HER NAME IS RACHEL HENDERSON.

12:13.863 --> 12:15.169
SHE'S AN ASPIRING ACTRESS.

12:15.299 --> 12:17.388
-OH, WELL, MAYBE THAT'S
HER STAGE NAME.

12:17.519 --> 12:18.912
-DID YOU GET AN ADDRESS?

12:19.521 --> 12:20.783
-YEAH, SHOULD BE
IN THE RESCUE CARD.

12:20.914 --> 12:22.393
BUT SHE'S GONNA BE
HERE ANY MINUTE.

12:23.568 --> 12:25.222
-WHY, DID YOU MAKE A DATE?

12:27.442 --> 12:28.965
-I LOANED HER $100.

12:29.749 --> 12:33.491
-$100? $100?

12:33.622 --> 12:34.710
-YEAH, SHE NEEDED
MONEY FOR HER HEAD SHOTS

12:34.841 --> 12:36.059
FOR HER AUDITION.

12:36.190 --> 12:38.192
-SO YOU GIVE HER
$100 JUST LIKE THAT?

12:38.322 --> 12:40.411
-SUMMER, STOP--
-SHE'S COMING THIS
MORNING TO PAY ME BACK.

12:40.542 --> 12:42.674
-GREAT, MATT, WHEN SHE GETS--
-HOW CAN YOU TRUST
A TOTAL STRANGER?

12:42.805 --> 12:44.024
-I GREW UP IN HOLLYWOOD.

12:44.154 --> 12:46.243
I THINK I KNOW
WHEN I SEE TALENT.

12:46.374 --> 12:48.289
-OH, REALLY?
WELL I HOPE SHE REMEMBERS
YOU WHEN SHE'S A BIG STAR.

12:48.419 --> 12:49.899
-SHE WILL.
-SUMMER: OH, REALLY?

12:50.508 --> 12:51.901
SO WHERE IS SHE?
-GUYS, UM--

12:52.032 --> 12:53.555
-SHE'S COMING.
-SUMMER: SURE.

12:53.685 --> 12:55.339
-WELL, WHEN SHE GETS
HERE WILL YOU LET ME KNOW

12:55.470 --> 12:56.776
SO I CAN CALL HER DAD?

12:59.213 --> 13:00.214
UH-OH!

13:03.870 --> 13:08.657
-[SOUL MUSIC PLAYING]

13:21.409 --> 13:24.325
-♪ EVERY SINGLE DAY

