♪ EVERY SINGLE DAY

15:27.665 --> 15:29.145
-OKAY, GREAT, THANKS.

15:31.756 --> 15:33.193
SO, WAS SHE HOME?

15:34.455 --> 15:35.325
-NOPE.

15:36.022 --> 15:36.892
-WHAT?

15:38.720 --> 15:39.764
-SHE WASN'T HOME.

15:40.417 --> 15:41.592
THERE WASN'T EVEN A HOME THERE.

15:42.593 --> 15:43.420
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

15:44.465 --> 15:46.684
-THERE WAS NO SEVEN FOUR SEVEN
OCEANFRONT WALK.

15:47.555 --> 15:49.774
-OH, SO YOU MEAN RACHEL
GAVE YOU A FAKE ADDRESS?

15:50.471 --> 15:51.646
OR IS IT NANCY?

15:52.777 --> 15:54.605
WELL, YOU SAID SHE WAS
A TALENTED ACTRESS.

15:54.736 --> 15:55.998
I GUESS YOU WERE RIGHT.

15:56.738 --> 15:57.826
-YOU KNOW WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS?

15:58.827 --> 15:59.741
YOU DON'T TRUST PEOPLE.

16:01.743 --> 16:03.484
-AND YOU PROBLEM IS YOU DO.

16:07.314 --> 16:08.663
-AS IT TURNS OUT WE THINK THAT

16:08.793 --> 16:10.752
ONE OF OUR LIFEGUARDS
MAY HAVE RESCUED

16:10.882 --> 16:13.015
YOUR DAUGHTER YESTERDAY.
-WELL, WHAT HAPPENED?
IS SHE ALL RIGHT?

16:13.146 --> 16:14.495
WHERE IS SHE NOW?
-HERE'S THE GUARD THAT
PULLED HER OUT OF THE WATER.

16:14.625 --> 16:17.367
MATT, THIS IS HENRY,
NANCY KREBS' FATHER.

16:17.498 --> 16:19.848
-OH, I WANT TO THANK YOU FOR
SAVING MY DAUGHTER'S LIFE.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.981
YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW GRATEFUL I AM.

16:22.111 --> 16:23.808
-WELL, I'M NOT ACTUALLY SURE
IT WAS YOUR DAUGHTER, SIR.

16:24.418 --> 16:27.290
-THE NAME SHE PUT ON HER RESCUE
CARD WAS RACHEL HENDERSON.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.466
-YEAH, I LOANED HER $100
AND SHE SAID SHE'D COME BACK

16:29.597 --> 16:31.773
THE NEXT MORNING,
BUT SHE NEVER SHOWED.

16:31.903 --> 16:34.515
AND THE ADDRESS SHE
GAVE ME DOESN'T EXIST.

16:35.124 --> 16:36.952
SO IT'S PROBABLY NOT
YOUR DAUGHTER. I'M SORRY.

16:37.083 --> 16:39.433
-NO, NO THAT SOUNDS LIKE NANCY.

16:39.955 --> 16:42.349
SHE HAS A WAY OF
GETTING WHAT SHE WANTS.

16:43.524 --> 16:45.265
-WELL, WE DISTRIBUTED
HER PHOTOGRAPH.

16:45.874 --> 16:46.788
AS SOON AS ONE OF
MY GUARDS SPOTS HER

16:46.918 --> 16:47.832
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW.

16:47.963 --> 16:49.182
-THANK YOU FOR YOUR HELP.

16:49.704 --> 16:51.271
I'M GOING TO SEND A
LETTER TO YOUR CHIEF

16:51.401 --> 16:53.969
AND TELL HIM JUST HOW
HELPFUL YOU'VE BOTH BEEN.

16:55.057 --> 16:56.319
GOD BLESS THE BOTH OF YOU.

17:00.019 --> 17:03.109
OH, AND YOUNG MAN, WHEN
I FIND MY DAUGHTER,

17:03.239 --> 17:04.935
YOU'LL GET THE $100 BACK.

17:05.502 --> 17:06.415
I PROMISE.

17:07.809 --> 17:08.766
-THANK YOU.

17:28.656 --> 17:29.570
THAT'S TODAY.

17:58.903 --> 18:02.081
-EXCUSE ME, THE YACHT,
A STAR OF HONG KONG.

18:02.211 --> 18:03.430
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED TO IT?

18:03.560 --> 18:05.171
IT WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE IN AT, LIKE, 3:30.

18:05.301 --> 18:07.869
-YEAH, NO, SHE RAN
INTO SOME BAD WEATHER.

18:07.999 --> 18:09.566
AFRAID SHE'S GONNA BE DELAYED.

18:09.697 --> 18:11.438
-DELAYED? HOW LONG?

18:12.265 --> 18:14.658
-SHOULD BE IN ABOUT THIS
TIME TOMORROW, I'D SAY.

18:30.109 --> 18:30.979
-HEY!

18:33.938 --> 18:36.985
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:07.320 --> 19:08.756
-OKAY, LET ME GO.

19:08.886 --> 19:10.061
-WHY'D YOU RUN AWAY?

19:10.192 --> 19:11.498
-LET ME GO!

19:14.675 --> 19:16.590
YOU LOOKED SO ANGRY.
IT SCARED ME.

19:17.939 --> 19:20.594
LOOK, COME ON, I KNOW--
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE MONEY.

19:20.724 --> 19:22.683
MY AUDITION TOOK
LONGER THAN EXPECTED.

19:22.813 --> 19:25.294
AND WHEN I GOT TO THE
RESTAURANT MY BOSS FIRED ME.

19:28.036 --> 19:30.343
I WAS TOO EMBARRASSED
TO SHOW UP EMPTY-HANDED.

19:31.953 --> 19:34.303
YOU PROBABLY THINK I RAN
OUT ON YOU, DON'T YOU.

19:34.434 --> 19:36.523
-YEAH, WELL, THE
THOUGHT CROSSED MY MIND.

19:37.654 --> 19:39.265
BUT THAT'S NOT WHY
I CHASED AFTER YOU.

19:40.004 --> 19:40.962
-IT'S NOT?

19:41.092 --> 19:42.616
-YOUR FATHER'S LOOKING FOR YOU.

19:43.791 --> 19:44.792
-MY FATHER.

19:47.925 --> 19:49.971
YOU DIDN'T TELL HIM
YOU SAW ME, DID YOU?

19:51.407 --> 19:52.321
-YES.

19:54.889 --> 19:56.456
HE NEEDS TO TALK TO YOU.

19:59.154 --> 20:00.634
YOUR FATHER IS DYING, RACHEL.

20:01.983 --> 20:03.114
OR IS IT NANCY?

20:03.941 --> 20:05.726
-MY FATHER'S NOT DYING.

20:05.856 --> 20:07.684
IT'S A TRICK SO YOU'LL
FEEL SORRY FOR HIM

20:07.815 --> 20:08.903
AND HELP HIM FIND ME.

20:09.469 --> 20:11.427
-YOU EXPECT ME TO
BELIEVE THAT, RIGHT?

20:11.558 --> 20:12.776
-RIGHT.

20:12.907 --> 20:14.648
-GIVE ME A BREAK.

20:14.778 --> 20:16.389
-IT'S TRUE.

20:17.694 --> 20:20.697
LOOK, MY NAME IS NANCY, OKAY.

20:22.133 --> 20:24.092
I LIED 'CAUSE MY
FATHER'S A MANIAC

20:24.223 --> 20:26.790
AND IF HE FINDS ME
HE'LL BEAT ME AGAIN.

20:26.921 --> 20:29.663
-COME ON, I MET YOUR FATHER.

20:30.272 --> 20:32.579
HE LOOKS LIKE THE MOST
GENTLE MAN I'VE EVER SEEN.

20:32.709 --> 20:35.364
-YOU CAN'T JUDGE
SOMEONE BY HOW THEY LOOK.

20:35.495 --> 20:36.583
HE'S AN ANIMAL.

20:37.279 --> 20:39.194
PLEASE, MATT, DON'T
LET HIM FIND ME.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.938
PLEASE DON'T TELL HIM ABOUT ME.

20:44.460 --> 20:45.505
-TELL HIM WHAT?

20:46.593 --> 20:48.203
THE FAKE ADDRESS YOU GAVE ME?

20:48.334 --> 20:50.292
-YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
HE HITS ME.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.989
THAT'S WHY I RAN AWAY.

20:53.164 --> 20:56.646
-HEY, I CAN'T FORCE YOU
TO DEAL WITH YOUR FATHER.

20:57.256 --> 20:58.909
BUT IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,

20:59.040 --> 21:00.520
YOU CAN REACH HIM THROUGH
THE BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

21:00.650 --> 21:02.478
-I'LL HAVE YOUR MONEY TOMORROW.

21:02.609 --> 21:03.740
WHEN DO YOU WORK?

21:04.393 --> 21:05.568
-I'M OFF TOMORROW.

21:06.352 --> 21:07.744
-WELL, WHEN CAN I FIND YOU?

21:08.528 --> 21:12.488
-I LIVE ON A BOAT NOT
FAR FROM HERE, SLIP 88.

21:13.141 --> 21:16.666
-88. I'LL BE THERE, I PROMISE.

21:19.016 --> 21:20.540
-I FOUND THIS IN THE DRYER.

21:22.846 --> 21:23.891
-THANKS.

21:24.021 --> 21:25.588
-I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

21:28.678 --> 21:29.810
-[SIGH]

21:33.379 --> 21:35.642
-[CHEERING]

21:39.994 --> 21:43.911
-[CHATTER]

22:03.583 --> 22:05.106
-ALL: READY, BREAK!

22:25.431 --> 22:27.215
-MAN: GO, GO!

22:41.577 --> 22:43.797
-[CHEERING]

22:43.927 --> 22:45.146
-YES!

22:45.276 --> 22:47.670
-ALL RIGHT!

22:50.499 --> 22:51.848
-[KNOCKING]

22:53.546 --> 22:54.416
-I GOT IT.

23:02.337 --> 23:03.599
HEY, STEPHANIE, COME ON IN.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.122
-HI, HOBIE, IS YOUR DAD IN?

23:05.253 --> 23:06.515
-YEAH, HE'S UPSTAIRS.

23:07.734 --> 23:08.517
DAD!

23:09.605 --> 23:11.781
SO, YOU WANT SOME CREAM SODA?

23:11.912 --> 23:13.435
-[LAUGHS] SURE.

23:17.047 --> 23:19.049
OH MY GOSH, WHERE
DID YOU GET ALL THIS?

23:19.180 --> 23:21.008
-REMEMBER THAT BOOGIE
BOARD COMPETITION I WON?

23:21.138 --> 23:22.792
-YEAH.

23:22.923 --> 23:24.794
-FIRST PRIZE WAS A YEAR'S
SUPPLY OF A&W CREAM SODA.

23:24.925 --> 23:25.795
THE JUST DELIVERED IT.

23:25.926 --> 23:27.014
-[LAUGHTER]

23:29.146 --> 23:30.670
-MITCH: HEY, STEPH.
-HI.

23:31.192 --> 23:34.804
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,
BUT I NEEDED TO TALK.

23:34.935 --> 23:35.805
-SURE.

23:37.328 --> 23:38.286
HOBESTER.

23:39.069 --> 23:40.419
-HAVE A NICE CHAT.

23:41.550 --> 23:42.551
-BUY YOU A CUP OF COFFEE?

23:42.682 --> 23:43.509
-OKAY.

23:48.514 --> 23:49.384
-SO?

23:51.691 --> 23:53.301
-IT'S NOTHING EARTH-SHATTERING.

23:54.607 --> 23:56.435
I JUST WANTED TO KNOW WHAT
YOU THOUGHT ABOUT SCOTT.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.525
-I THINK HE'S A GREAT GUY.

24:00.439 --> 24:02.745
-HE IS, HE'S REALLY TERRIFIC.

24:03.398 --> 24:05.008
-SO THEN WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

24:05.139 --> 24:10.231
-WELL, THE PROBLEM IS
THAT HE'S IN THE MILITARY.

24:11.014 --> 24:12.494
AFTER WHAT MY
MOTHER WENT THROUGH,

24:13.016 --> 24:14.844
I MEAN, SHE NEVER
REALLY RECOVERED WHEN

24:14.975 --> 24:16.280
MY FATHER DIED IN THE WAR.

24:16.933 --> 24:18.195
I SWORE THAT I WOULD
NEVER GET INVOLVED

24:18.326 --> 24:19.719
WITH A MAN IN THE MILITARY.

24:19.849 --> 24:22.591
-STEPHANIE, WE'RE NOT AT WAR.

24:22.722 --> 24:26.203
-I KNOW, BUT STILL,
IT'S NOT A STABLE LIFE.

24:26.813 --> 24:29.337
YOU MOVE AROUND ALL THE TIME.
THERE'S NO SENSE OF SECURITY,

24:30.469 --> 24:32.471
AND I DON'T WANT TO RAISE
MY KIDS IN THAT KIND
OF ENVIRONMENT.

24:33.123 --> 24:36.387
-WAIT A MINUTE, YOU TWO ARE
ALREADY TALKING MARRIAGE?

24:36.518 --> 24:38.607
-NO. I MEAN, NOT REALLY.

24:40.740 --> 24:42.829
I JUST FIND MYSELF
HOLDING BACK WITH HIM.

24:43.525 --> 24:44.395
-WHY?

24:48.399 --> 24:51.272
-MAYBE BECAUSE DEEP DOWN INSIDE

24:51.402 --> 24:52.621
THERE'S THIS THOUGHT THAT MAYBE

24:53.796 --> 24:55.624
YOU AND I MIGHT GET
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN.

25:05.460 --> 25:06.853
-STEPHANIE.

25:06.983 --> 25:08.332
-I'M NOT SAYING I
REALLY FEEL THAT WAY.

25:08.463 --> 25:09.856
I JUST SOMETIME THINK IT.

25:10.596 --> 25:13.512
-WE WOULDN'T WANNA RUIN A
GREAT FRIENDSHIP, NOW, WOULD WE.

25:15.949 --> 25:18.865
-NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

25:19.909 --> 25:21.607
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE
SURE YOU FELT THAT WAY

25:21.737 --> 25:25.785
BEFORE I STARTED THINKING
SERIOUSLY ABOUT SCOTT.

25:31.138 --> 25:33.662
WELL, THANKS FOR PUTTING
UP WITH MY INSANITY.

25:33.793 --> 25:34.620
-COME HERE, COME HERE.

25:37.361 --> 25:38.449
-[LAUGHS]

25:39.712 --> 25:41.627
IT'S OKAY, I'M USED TO IT.

25:43.977 --> 25:44.891
HEY STEPH?

25:47.067 --> 25:47.937
GOOD NIGHT.

25:53.508 --> 25:54.509
[SIGH]

26:30.458 --> 26:33.374
-RACHEL. I MEAN NANCY.

26:34.244 --> 26:35.376
-MATT, I NEED YOUR HELP.

26:35.506 --> 26:37.073
I HAVE NO ONE ELSE TO TURN TO.

26:37.726 --> 26:38.597
-WHAT'S WRONG?

26:39.902 --> 26:40.860
-IT'S MY FATHER.

26:41.774 --> 26:43.732
I KNOW HE SEEMS HARMLESS,

26:43.863 --> 26:45.516
BUT IF I TOLD YOU HALF
THE THINGS HE'S DONE

26:45.647 --> 26:46.953
YOU'D WANT TO RIP HIS HEART OUT.

26:47.649 --> 26:48.955
-WELL, IF HE'S THAT BAD,

26:49.085 --> 26:50.043
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GO TO THE POLICE?

26:50.913 --> 26:52.088
-'CAUSE IT WOULDN'T
DO ANY GOOD.

26:52.219 --> 26:53.699
MY FATHER'S A PATHOLOGICAL LIAR.

26:53.829 --> 26:55.396
HE'D JUST DENY
EVERYTHING THAT I SAID.

26:56.876 --> 26:58.094
-WELL, WHAT CAN I DO?

26:58.921 --> 27:00.270
-I HAVE TO GO BACK
TO THE YACHT CLUB.

27:00.401 --> 27:01.402
COULD YOU COME WITH ME?

27:03.709 --> 27:04.884
IT'S YOUR DAY OFF, ISN'T IT?

27:06.015 --> 27:07.974
-WHAT'S AT THE YACHT CLUB?

27:08.104 --> 27:10.237
-I HAVE A PACKAGE THAT'S
ARRIVING ON A YACHT
THAT DOCKS THERE.

27:10.367 --> 27:12.065
THAT'S WHAT THE BILL
OF TRANSPORT WAS FOR.

27:12.848 --> 27:13.893
I TRIED TO PICK IT UP YESTERDAY

27:14.023 --> 27:15.634
BUT IT WAS DELAYED UNTIL TODAY.

27:16.243 --> 27:18.027
-WHAT'S IN THE PACKAGE?

27:18.158 --> 27:19.681
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW, IT WAS A
GIFT FROM MY AUNT CHARLOTTE.

27:19.812 --> 27:21.640
SHE'S CONSTANTLY TRAVELING
AND SHE ALWAYS SENDS ME

27:21.770 --> 27:22.945
THESE EXOTIC GIFTS.

27:24.077 --> 27:25.165
I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE WHAT IT IS.

27:27.471 --> 27:28.647
WILL YOU PLEASE COME?

27:31.258 --> 27:33.390
I PROMISE IT'LL BE THE LAST
FAVOR I EVER ASK OF YOU.

27:33.956 --> 27:34.870
I CROSS MY HEART.

27:36.742 --> 27:38.134
-I'LL GO ON ONE CONDITION.

27:38.831 --> 27:40.833
THAT AFTER WE GO
AND GET THE PACKAGE,

27:40.963 --> 27:43.052
YOU GO WITH ME TO SEE YOUR
FATHER AND DEAL WITH IT.

27:47.230 --> 27:48.101
-OKAY.

27:49.232 --> 27:50.233
BUT ONLY IF YOU'RE THERE.

27:50.364 --> 27:51.582
-I'LL BE THERE.

28:31.797 --> 28:34.364
-OKAY, AND BE SURE YOU TAKE THE
ENTIRE MEDICAL KIT, OKAY.

28:34.495 --> 28:35.409
ALL RIGHT.

28:35.539 --> 28:37.280
-SUMMER: MITCH.
-YO.

28:37.411 --> 28:39.979
-I SAW THAT GIRL RACHEL OR
NANCY OR WHATEVER HER NAME IS.

28:40.109 --> 28:41.154
-WHERE?

28:41.284 --> 28:43.156
-IN THE MARINA ON MATT'S BOAT.

28:43.286 --> 28:44.984
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
IS GOING ON THERE

28:45.114 --> 28:46.507
BUT I THINK YOU
BETTER TALK TO HIM.

28:47.377 --> 28:49.945
-HIS BOAT'S STILL
IN SLIP 88, ISN'T IT?

28:50.076 --> 28:51.294
-YEAH.

28:51.425 --> 28:52.208
-OKAY, I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN FIND OUT.

28:52.339 --> 28:52.992
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

28:53.122 --> 28:53.949
-OKAY.

28:57.387 --> 29:02.001
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

29:24.327 --> 29:26.068
-EXCUSE THE MESS.
I JUST MOVED IN.

29:28.244 --> 29:29.376
-GOD, I'M SO EXCITED!

29:29.506 --> 29:30.681
-[LAUGHS]

29:43.869 --> 29:45.000
PORCELAIN DOLLS.

29:45.131 --> 29:46.001
-[LAUGHS]

29:46.741 --> 29:49.048
-MY AUNT KNOWS HOW
MUCH I LOVE DOLLS.

29:49.178 --> 29:51.224
-YEAH, THERE MUST BE
20 OF THEM IN THERE.

29:52.181 --> 29:53.269
-I WANT YOU TO HAVE ONE.

29:54.444 --> 29:55.532
-OH, GREAT.

29:57.186 --> 29:58.884
-THEY'RE WORTH MORE THAN $100.

29:59.536 --> 30:00.668
-SURE.

30:00.799 --> 30:01.800
-[KNOCKING]

30:03.497 --> 30:04.454
-YOU EXPECTING SOMEONE?

30:05.107 --> 30:06.108
-NO.

30:09.938 --> 30:10.809
WHO'S THERE?

30:16.989 --> 30:17.859
-SAM.

30:18.991 --> 30:19.861
-SAM?

30:19.992 --> 30:21.341
-HELLO, LINDA.

30:21.471 --> 30:22.951
-LINDA?

30:23.082 --> 30:23.996
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:24.126 --> 30:24.953
-SHUT UP.

30:26.476 --> 30:27.869
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
I'VE GONE THROUGH

30:28.000 --> 30:28.827
TRYING TO FIND YOU.

30:33.222 --> 30:35.616
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE IT'S
BEEN TIME WELL SPENT.

30:45.060 --> 30:46.757
JUST SHUT UP AND LISTEN TO ME.

30:46.888 --> 30:48.585
I'LL BE THERE IN
EXACTLY ONE HOUR.

30:48.716 --> 30:50.065
DON'T KEEP ME WAITING.

30:51.414 --> 30:53.286
ALL RIGHT, WHICH
DOLL ARE THEY IN?

30:54.591 --> 30:56.071
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

30:56.202 --> 30:57.638
-THE DIAMONDS!

31:01.990 --> 31:04.123
-I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
HE'S TALKING ABOUT.

31:05.864 --> 31:08.040
-YOU KNOW, YOU'RE
LOOKING AT THE GREATEST

31:08.170 --> 31:11.086
CON ARTIST IN THE
WORLD, A CHILD PRODIGY.

31:12.174 --> 31:13.567
-I TOLD YOU HE WAS CRAZY.

31:13.697 --> 31:15.264
-BUT I'M GONNA LET
YOU IN ON SOMETHING.

31:15.395 --> 31:16.526
SHE'S NOT MY DAUGHTER.

31:16.657 --> 31:18.137
SHE WAS MY PARTNER.

31:18.267 --> 31:19.965
-LIAR!

31:20.095 --> 31:22.532
-UNTIL SHE GOT GREEDY AND
RIPPED ME OFF IN HONG KONG.

31:22.663 --> 31:24.317
-MATT, DO SOMETHING.

31:24.447 --> 31:25.840
-WHAT?

31:25.971 --> 31:27.711
-NOW, GIVE ME THE DOLL
WITH THE DIAMONDS IN IT

31:27.842 --> 31:29.496
OR I'M GONNA SHOOT YOUR FRIEND.

31:35.067 --> 31:35.894
-GO AHEAD.

31:37.896 --> 31:39.201
-COLD AS ICE.

31:42.813 --> 31:44.772
-YOU THINK I CARE
WHAT HAPPENS TO HIM?

31:47.818 --> 31:49.646
-THIS PUTS YOU IN
AN AWKWARD POSITION.

31:50.430 --> 31:52.084
'CAUSE I GOTTA CATCH A BOAT.

31:54.303 --> 31:56.958
-COME ON, WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE HIM WHAT HE WANTS.

32:03.878 --> 32:04.748
-ONE...

32:08.622 --> 32:09.492
TWO...

32:10.624 --> 32:13.540
-WAIT, JUST DON'T DO
ANYTHING STUPID, OKAY.

32:15.237 --> 32:16.151
I'LL GIVE YOU THE DOLL.

32:16.760 --> 32:18.284
-OH, YOU SURPRISED ME.

32:18.414 --> 32:19.720
YOU DO HAVE A HEART.

32:23.028 --> 32:24.464
COME ON, COME ON.

32:36.215 --> 32:37.999
YOU ARE SO CLEVER.

32:39.870 --> 32:41.568
THAT'S WHAT I LOVE ABOUT YOU.

33:04.721 --> 33:08.987
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:33.114 --> 34:34.637
-DID YOU SEE WHERE
THAT BOAT WENT?

34:35.551 --> 34:36.813
-OH, YOU JUST MISSED THEM,

34:36.944 --> 34:38.293
THEY PULLED OUT
ABOUT 15 MINUTES AGO.

34:38.424 --> 34:39.599
-OKAY, THANKS.

35:04.189 --> 35:05.059
-HERE!

35:16.505 --> 35:18.028
WELL, HERE'S WHERE
WE PART COMPANY.

35:18.855 --> 35:20.161
I'M GLAD NO ONE GOT HURT.

35:21.293 --> 35:22.207
GOODBYE, LINDA.

35:24.426 --> 35:26.689
IT'S TOO BAD FOR YOU
THINGS HAD TO END THIS WAY.

35:28.126 --> 35:30.954
YOU TRULY ARE ONE OF THE
GREAT GRIFTERS OF ALL TIME.

35:50.539 --> 35:51.584
-NEWMIE, OVER THERE.

36:12.605 --> 36:14.259
HENRY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

36:14.389 --> 36:16.696
-OH, MATT AND RACHEL,
THEY'RE DOWN BELOW.

36:16.826 --> 36:18.480
SOMETHING TERRIBLE HAPPENED.

36:18.611 --> 36:19.177
YOU BETTER GET DOWN THERE,
SEE IF YOU CAN HELP THEM.

36:19.307 --> 36:20.265
-WHAT HAPPENED?

36:20.395 --> 36:21.483
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

36:21.614 --> 36:22.963
FIND OUT FOR YOURSELF.

36:23.093 --> 36:23.964
-OKAY.

36:25.748 --> 36:30.188
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

37:02.307 --> 37:04.222
-MY DIAMONDS!

37:13.840 --> 37:17.583
-HEY, TURN AROUND, RIGHT NOW.

37:50.659 --> 37:51.747
-MATT, UNTIE ME.

37:52.444 --> 37:53.532
-UNTIE WHO.

37:53.662 --> 37:55.447
-[SIGH] MATT.

37:58.014 --> 37:59.059
HUH?

37:59.189 --> 38:00.190
NANCY?

38:01.191 --> 38:03.890
OR IS IT RACHEL? OR
MAYBE IS IT LINDA?

38:06.196 --> 38:08.155
-LOOK, MY NAME'S LINDA, OKAY?

38:10.375 --> 38:11.898
HE GOT ME INTO THIS
WHEN I WAS YOUNG.

38:12.028 --> 38:13.595
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT I WAS DOING.

38:17.643 --> 38:20.080
COME ON, MATT, UNTIE ME, PLEASE.

38:25.694 --> 38:26.913
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

38:27.043 --> 38:28.218
-YEAH.

38:28.871 --> 38:29.655
DID YOU CATCH HIM?

38:29.785 --> 38:30.830
-YEAH.

38:32.092 --> 38:33.441
YEAH, HE ALMOST
GOT AWAY WITH IT.

38:34.790 --> 38:36.139
BUT WHEN HE CALLED HER
RACHEL INSTEAD OF NANCY

38:36.270 --> 38:37.184
I KNEW SOMETHING WAS OFF.

38:37.315 --> 38:38.316
-IT IS.

38:38.446 --> 38:41.319
MITCH, MEET LINDA.

38:42.407 --> 38:43.582
SHE'S HIS PARTNER.

39:07.736 --> 39:08.563
-HEY.

39:09.303 --> 39:10.130
-HI.

39:10.826 --> 39:11.784
-SO WHAT'S THE NEWS?

39:11.914 --> 39:12.915
WHAT'S HAPPENING WITH SCOTT?

39:15.396 --> 39:17.224
-DID YOU AND GAYLE LIVE
TOGETHER BEFORE YOU GOT MARRIED?

39:17.920 --> 39:20.009
-WELL, I GUESS THAT
ANSWERS MY QUESTION.

39:21.446 --> 39:24.579
-NO, NO. GAYLE
DIDN'T BELIEVE IN IT.

39:24.710 --> 39:26.189
-I DON'T THINK I DO EITHER.

39:28.409 --> 39:30.368
I GUESS I'M JUST TOO
MUCH OF A TRADITIONALIST.

39:30.890 --> 39:32.152
-YOU KNOW, STEPHANIE,
WHY DON'T YOU JUST

39:32.282 --> 39:34.023
DO YOURSELF A FAVOR, HUH?

39:34.154 --> 39:36.678
LIGHTEN UP, DON'T
BE SO ANALYTICAL.

39:36.809 --> 39:39.246
I MEAN, COME ON, JUST
GO WITH THE FLOW, YOU KNOW?

39:39.377 --> 39:40.334
GO WITH THE FLOW.

39:41.117 --> 39:42.205
-I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

39:43.598 --> 39:45.644
I'VE GOT TO STOP BEING
SO HARD ON MYSELF.

39:45.774 --> 39:49.996
I SHOULD JUST LET IT HAPPEN,
AND ENJOY FALLING IN LOVE.

39:50.126 --> 39:51.606
-ABSOLUTELY.

39:51.737 --> 39:53.478
THAT WOULD DEFINITELY
BE MY RECOMMENDATION.

39:56.655 --> 39:57.525
-SCOTT!

39:58.091 --> 39:59.397
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:01.137 --> 40:02.312
-I CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.

40:03.139 --> 40:04.227
I'M BEING SHIPPED OUT.

40:05.490 --> 40:07.883
-SHIPPED OUT? WHERE?

40:08.014 --> 40:11.409
-ANTARCTICA. TO AN ICEBREAKER.

40:11.539 --> 40:13.280
-ANTARCTICA.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.977
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

40:15.891 --> 40:18.807
THE LAST GUY SHE LIKED
BLEW OUT HIS KNEE,

40:18.938 --> 40:21.288
AND YOU'RE BEING SHIPPED
OUT TO THE SOUTH POLE.

40:22.942 --> 40:24.683
THE STEPHANIE HOLDEN
JINX STRIKES AGAIN.

40:25.205 --> 40:27.294
-I PROMISE I'LL
WRITE YOU EVERY DAY.

40:27.425 --> 40:28.861
-OH GOD.

40:28.991 --> 40:31.037
-WHAT ELSE IS THERE
TO DO IN ANTARCTICA?

40:37.130 --> 40:38.479
-YOU CONMEN!

40:38.610 --> 40:40.786
-[LAUGHTER]

40:42.091 --> 40:43.702
-MITCH, I'M GONNA
GET YOU FOR THIS!

40:43.832 --> 40:46.052
SCOTT, I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS!

40:47.836 --> 40:49.838
-COME ON, MATT,
LET'S DIVE FOR THEM.

40:50.404 --> 40:52.188
-SUMMER, THEY'RE AT
THE BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN.

40:53.233 --> 40:55.627
-I KNOW, BUT THEY'RE
DIAMONDS, MATT.

40:56.192 --> 40:57.106
-WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?

40:57.977 --> 40:59.021
THEY'RE PROBABLY STOLEN.

40:59.718 --> 41:02.198
-I KNOW BUT I JUST,
I JUST WANT ONE.

41:03.591 --> 41:05.114
-ONE? WHY?

41:06.681 --> 41:07.987
-TO PUT IN A RING.

41:09.684 --> 41:10.511
-IS THIS A CON?

41:11.860 --> 41:13.732
-DO I LOOK LIKE
A CONWOMAN TO YOU?

41:15.429 --> 41:17.344
[LAUGHTER]

41:34.230 --> 41:38.017
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
